The paper discusses the estimation of parameters of a Bayesian network, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes new approaches to improve the estimation process, which falls under the category of optimization and learning (cs.LG). The paper deals with incomplete data, which is a common problem in data management and analysis (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of entropy and Bayesian model averaging, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and statistical inference (cs.SI), respectively.
